            {
              "type": "space"
            }
          ],
          "answer": {
            "type": "number"
          }
        },
        {
          "label": "(b)",
          "marks": 2,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "content": "On day one, 50 people donated money to the charity. Each day, 20 more people donated to the charity than did so on the previous day, so that 70 people donated money on day two, 90 people donated money on day three, and so on."
            },
            {
              "type": "newline"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "content": "Find the number of people who donated to the charity on day fifteen."
            },
            {
              "type": "space"
            }
          ],
          "answer": {
            "type": "number"
          }
        },
        {
          "label": "(c)",
          "marks": 3,
          "content": [
            {
              "type": "text",
              "content": "Each day, the donation given by each person was £5"
            },
            {
              "type": "newline"
            },
            {
              "type": "text",
              "content": "Find the total amount of money donated by the end of day fifteen."
            },
            {
              "type": "space"
            }
          ],
          "answer": {
            "type": "number"
          }
        }
      ],
      "answer": null,
      "meta": {}
